The paper deals with optimization problems related to graphs, specifically vector domination and total vector domination. These problems are related to graph theory and algorithms, which are covered in several sub-categories of arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper deals with optimization problems and algorithms for graphs. The second likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as the paper discusses the approximability of the problems and their relationship to P=NP. The third likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as the paper deals with optimization problems on graphs. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as the paper discusses geometric interpretations of the problems. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as the paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems on graphs.
